"n.微薄的薪俸，少量的收入 【英】 n.微薄的薪俸,少量的 收入(small allowance or wage) 【考】 反义词：cornucopia( 富饶) 【例】 He had received a mere pittance of education.(他只受过 一点儿教育) n. 微薄的薪俸; 少量津贴; 很少的数额 = remuneration 【记】原指: 给和尚或穷人的食品施舍, 引申为少量津贴. Pit一小口, tan痰, ce: 朝乞丐的手里吐痰－少量的施舍－少量津贴 【类】pittance: allowance[money] = rivulet: stream少量津贴: 津贴 = 小溪: 溪流 【反】cornucopia(n 富饶); crop(n 庄稼; 收成) 【记】pity + ounce 可怜的一盎司，很少，每月只挣一盎司银子 pittance (n.)  c.1200, ""pious donation to a religious house or order to provide extra food; the extra food provided,"" also ""a small portion, scanty rations,"" from Old French pitance ""pity, mercy, compassion; refreshment, nourishment; portion of food allowed a monk or poor person by a pious bequest,"" apparently literally ""pity,"" from pitié (see pity). Meaning ""small amount, portion"" first recorded 1560s."
